    "description": {
      "value": "\r\n<p><b>Price</b> 2 gp; <b>Weight</b> 2 lbs.</p>\r\n<p>This leather or hemp harness allows a holder to restrain and control a domesticated animal. A harness is standard equipment for anyone trying to teach an animal tricks with the Handle Animal skill. Ready-made harnesses are available in most markets for common domesticated animals such as cats, dogs, horses, and oxen, but harnesses can be made for nearly any creature.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><i>Training Harness</i>: This specialized harness must be tailored to a specific type of <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Animal\">animal</a>. A training harness provides a +2 bonus on <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/handle-animal\">Handle Animal</a> checks made with an <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/creature-types#TOC-Animal\">animal</a> wearing it.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n",
